the triggering note by the same increment)\
\
\
\
C. OPTION 2:\'ca At given moments (perhaps according to a timed process?), certain\
chords should be "arpeggiated", i.e., the notes articulated one by one.\'ca Once\
you've figured this out, try to make the rhythm of the arpeggiation variable, as\
well, perhaps, as the order in which the notes occur.\
\
Objects you might need include:\'ca \'95\'c0\uc0\u189  gate \'95\'c0\u189  or \'95\'c0\u189  switch \'95\'c0\u189 ; \'95\'c0\u189  unpack \'95\'c0\u189 \
(new to us);\'ca \'95\'c0\uc0\u189  pipe \'95\'c0\u189 ; possibly \'95\'c0\u189  counter \'95\'c0\u189  or \'95\'c0\u189  clocker \'95\'c0\u189  (also\
new to us) for automated triggering of the arpeggiation. \
\
\
D.\'ca Try to make the instrument as "musical" as possible.\'ca (Prioritize insofar as\
possible what YOU think a musically compelling result entails and realize those\
instrumental capabilities in that order.)}